				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">All instructions are always finished before any interrupts. NMI has always priority to the IRQ, and nobody can ever disable the NMI in software. The NMI will interrupt all IRQs being executed. IRQs will interupt an NMI being exectued only if the I flag has been manually clear inside of the NMI routine.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
