					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't know how "perfect" you're trying to be but... it's after the last (effective) cycle of the current instruction. Yes, I know there are some oddities as fetching the next byte and throwing it away but... that's the idea. 
<br />
<br />In other words, do not trigger interrupts in the middle of an instruction. Obviously the flag might go up during that time, but it doesn't imply to be triggered THAT time.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><strong>Zepper</strong><br /><a href="http://rocknes.web.fc2.com/" class="postlink"><em>RockNES developer</em></a></div>
