				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It depends on when IRQ/NMI assertion occurs during the indicated cycle. Early in that cycle, the interrupt will be vectored before instruction 2, and this vectoring will begin during cycle 4 of the first instruction (meaning that instruction 1 in the case would probably be something like LDA zero-page). If late in the indicated cycle, and the interrupt will be vectored after instruction 2.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

